{
  "texts": [
    "To ensure the reliability of the rv r0 data, we cross-check the values of rv r0 from the red band and the values of rv b0 from the blue band.",
    "For most MRS spectra, the values of rv r0 and rv b0 are consistent with each other.",
    "A few MRS spectra do have large differences between their rv r0 and rv b0 values, which are considered to be unreliable.",
    "In this work, we use the criterion of |rv r0rv b0| ≥ 7 km/s to identify unreliable radial velocity data.",
    "The threshold of the criterion (7 km/s) corresponds to about one pixel of wavelength shift in the Hα band of MRS. Those spectra with radial velocity data meeting the criterion are removed from our sample."
  ]
}